{"type":null,"faqId":26426,"title":"Ten Bad Habits of Using Your Phone","answer":"<p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';text-align:center\" align=\"center\"><b><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman','serif';\ncolor:#333333\">Ten Bad Habits of Using Your Phone</span></b></p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif'\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';text-align:left;\nword-break:break-all\" align=\"left\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman','serif';\ncolor:#333333;\">As smartphones are getting more and more\nintelligent, they bring us convenient and risks at the same time. This document\nlists ten issues you may have ignored. </span></p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';text-align:left;\nword-break:break-all\" align=\"left\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';text-align:left;\nword-break:break-all\" align=\"left\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman','serif';\ncolor:#333333;\">Bad habit 1: The transaction limit for your\nphone's online banking account is high. </span></p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';text-align:left;\nword-break:break-all\" align=\"left\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman','serif';\ncolor:#333333;\">Nowadays, to facilitate your operation,\nsome online payment does not require a password. However, what if your phone is\nlost? The risk is even higher if you do not set a password for your phone. </span></p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';text-align:left;\nword-break:break-all\" align=\"left\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';text-align:left;\nword-break:break-all\" align=\"left\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman','serif';\ncolor:#333333;\">Bad habit 2: Your phone is not attached\nwith a protective film. </span></p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';text-align:left;\nword-break:break-all\" align=\"left\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman','serif';\ncolor:#333333;\">You are advised to attach a protective film\nto protect your phone from scratches. In addition, if your phone is dropped to\nthe ground, the protective film can prevent the screen from being broken. </span></p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';text-align:left;\nword-break:break-all\" align=\"left\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';text-align:left;\nword-break:break-all\" align=\"left\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman','serif';\ncolor:#333333;\">Bad habit 3: Your phone is not cleaned\nregularly. </span></p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';text-align:left;\nword-break:break-all\" align=\"left\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman','serif';\ncolor:#333333;\">Phones have more bacteria than toilets.\nClean your phone from time to time. </span></p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';text-align:left;\nword-break:break-all\" align=\"left\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';text-align:left;\nword-break:break-all\" align=\"left\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman','serif';\ncolor:#333333;\">Bad habit 4: Charge the phone only after\nthe battery power is depleted. </span></p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';text-align:left;\nword-break:break-all\" align=\"left\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman','serif';\ncolor:#333333;\">Charging your phone only after the battery\npower is depleted significantly reduces your battery's lifespan. Charge your\nphone once the battery level is lower than 20%.</span></p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';text-align:left;\nword-break:break-all\" align=\"left\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';text-align:left;\nword-break:break-all\" align=\"left\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman','serif';\ncolor:#333333;\">Bad habit 5: Your phone is not backed up\nregularly. </span><span style=\"font-family:'Microsoft YaHei','sans-serif';\ncolor:#333333;\"><br>\n</span><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman','serif';\ncolor:#333333;\">Important data, such as your contacts and\nphotos, should be backed up regularly, because your phone needs to be formatted\nwhen you encounter exceptions. </span></p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';text-align:left;\nword-break:break-all\" align=\"left\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';text-align:left;\nword-break:break-all\" align=\"left\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman','serif';\ncolor:#333333;\">Bad habit 6: Use your phone while driving. </span></p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';text-align:left;\nword-break:break-all\" align=\"left\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman','serif';\ncolor:#333333;\">For your safety, wear a headset and\nmicrophone if you have to make calls while driving. </span></p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';text-align:left;\nword-break:break-all\" align=\"left\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';text-align:left;\nword-break:break-all\" align=\"left\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman','serif';\ncolor:#333333;\">Bad habit 7: Connect to unknown Wi-Fi\nhotspots. </span></p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';text-align:left;\nword-break:break-all\" align=\"left\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman','serif';\ncolor:#333333;\">Your browse history and other personal data\nmay be maliciously copied when you are enjoying a free Wi-Fi access. Use\ntrusted Wi-Fi hotspots only. </span></p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';text-align:left;\nword-break:break-all\" align=\"left\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';text-align:left;\nword-break:break-all\" align=\"left\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman','serif';\ncolor:#333333;\">Bad habit 8: Never turn off your Wi-Fi and\nGPS. </span></p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';text-align:left;\nword-break:break-all\" align=\"left\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman','serif';\ncolor:#333333;\">Wi-Fi and GPS are power-intensive. Turn\nthem off if you do not need them to maximize your phone's standby time. </span></p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';text-align:left;\nword-break:break-all\" align=\"left\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';text-align:left;\nword-break:break-all\" align=\"left\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman','serif';\ncolor:#333333;\">Bad habit 9: Scan QR codes from untrusted\nparties. </span></p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';text-align:left;\nword-break:break-all\" align=\"left\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman','serif';\ncolor:#333333;\">Scanning QR codes from untrusted parties\nmay expose yourself to deception. Before you scan a QR code, check its usage\nand make sure it is provided by official accounts. </span></p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';text-align:left;\nword-break:break-all\" align=\"left\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';text-align:left;\nword-break:break-all\" align=\"left\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman','serif';\ncolor:#333333;\">Bad habit 10: Set SNS accounts to\nauto-login. </span></p>\n<p style=\"margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-size:10.5pt;font-family:'Calibri','sans-serif';text-align:left;\nword-break:break-all\" align=\"left\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman','serif';\ncolor:#333333;\">If your phone is lost, your personal data\nmay be leaked. </span></p>\n<br>\n</p>","faqTypeId":null,"faqType":null,"useful":0,"unUseful":0,"languageId":1,"languageName":"en","faqCode":"825","faqTypeCode":null,"isTop":"0","moduleCode":"faq","productId":null,"productCode":null,"postDate":1433165162000,"seriesProductName":"","visitedTimes":41,"isUsefulFlag":null,"score":0,"times":0,"imageList":null,"displayType":"text","justView":"0","fileName":null,"filePath":null,"imagePath":null,"imageName":null,"productIdList":null,"curPage":null,"pageSize":null,"siteCode":null,"statusFlag":"Publish","returnCode":0,"totalRows":null,"keywords":"Ten Bad Habits of Using Your Phone","avgScore":0.0,"createDate":null,"totalPages":null}